history.content:
There's no good way to answer that question. I have never tracked that data point. People will continue to add/drop classes until the deadline which is Feb 13th at midnight.

Although the intention of the fee is to motivate students to make changes earlier in the semester so wait listed students have a better chance to get into classes they really want, I've not seen a noticeable difference in drop behavior once the fee kicks in.

children.subject: You would have to talk to the Registrar about that since I do not create nor collect these fees.

"Although the intention of the fee is to motivate students to make changes earlier in the semester so wait listed students have a better chance to get into classes they really want, I've not seen a noticeable difference in drop behavior once the fee kicks in."

What is the point of the fee? It seems unnecessary with this fact alone.

history.content: If this gives you any hope, Shewchuck recently posted the following on Piazza: "I didn't think the undergrad waitlist would empty out, but now that the CS 189 waitlist is down to 73, it seems possible it might clear.  If so, we'll start admitting grad students after that."
I'm on the waitlist for 189 and trying to figure out if I should keep waiting.
